<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:og="http://ogp.me/ns#"
      xmlns:fb="http://www.facebook.com/2008/fbml">

<head>
  <title>Group Hug | Sponsored by Engine Yard</title>
  
    <meta property="og:title" content="Ruby on Rails application for posting messages to Facebook"/>
    <meta property="og:type" content="website"/>
    <meta property="og:url" content="http://icanhazrails.com/"/>
    <meta property="og:image" content="http://icanhazrails.com/images/eyuflag.jpg"/>
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Group Hug | Sponsored by Engine Yard"/>
    <meta property="og:description"
          content="Group Hug is a Ruby on Rails application for posting messages to Facebook. It was built by Sergey Kornitsky and Matt Reider as a learning exercise. The Readme file, printed below, serves as a tutorial on how to build Group Hug from scratch."/>
  
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag :all %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag :defaults %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tag %>
  <script> 
  <%= yield (:javascript) %>
  </script>
</head>
<body>
	<a href="https://github.com/mreider/group-hug"><img style="position: absolute; top: 0; right: 0; border: 0;" src="https://assets1.github.com/img/30f550e0d38ceb6ef5b81500c64d970b7fb0f028?repo=&url=http%3A%2F%2Fs3.amazonaws.com%2Fgithub%2Fribbons%2Fforkme_right_orange_ff7600.png&path=" alt="Fork me on GitHub"></a>
  	<div id="wrap">
	<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td valign="top" width="400"><h1><img src="/images/lolhug.jpg"> <a href="http://icanhazrails.com">Group Hug</a></h1></td>
		<td width="20">&nbsp;</td>
		<td valign="top" width="255">
			<h4>Learn Ruby on Rails with <br>Engine Yard University</h4>
			Visit <a href="http://engineyard.com/university">http://engineyard.com/university</a> for training courses, screencasts, and more.
		</td>
		<td valign="top">
				<img hspace="0" src="/images/eyuflag.jpg"/>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
	<p>
						<% if current_facebook_user !=nil %>
							<%= fb_logout_link("Logout", request.url) %><br />
							<% else
							# you must explicitly request permissions for facebook user fields
							# here we instruct facebook to ask the user for permission for our website
							# to access the user's facebook email and birthday, groups,read_stream
							%>
							<div class="clues">
							Learning Rails is easiest if it is done in the context of a real application. Group Hug is a simple Rails application (written by Sergey Kornitsky and Matt Reider), built as a learning tool. The README file, printed below, serves as a tutorial on how to build Group Hug from scratch.<br><br>The application has three simple requirements.
						  <ol> 
							<li>Esers can login using Facebook Connect</li>
							<li>Users choose from their Facebook Groups</li>
							<li>Users post messages to their groups</li>
						  </ol>
							</div>
							<br clear="left"><table><tr><td><%= fb_login_and_redirect( url_for(:action => 'create', :controller => 'user', :only_path => false),:perms => 'email,user_birthday,user_groups,read_stream, publish_stream') %></td><td>to try the group hug application + post messages<td></tr></table> 
							<% end %>
						</p>
		<%= "Welcome #{@current_user.name}!"  if @current_user !=nil %>
		<%= yield %>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	</div>	

  <%= fb_connect_async_js %>



</body>
</html>
